task.summary: Implemented model (classes that define tables using ebean)

Added class for salted hashing: call PasswordHash.createHash with the plaintext password and put that in the database, and to check call PasswordHash.validatePassword with the plaintext password that the user entered and the stored correct hash
Using own hashing class instead of BGCrypt
Works now after couple of fixes
Works now after couple of fixes
Updated table schemes according to Neda's suggestion
Workaround for not working composite key
Geolocation works. If you're on localhost, this obviously can't work.
User identification based on cookie works. When the user visits the Index page, a random cookie is generated, which is always sent with every request to the server (standard behaviour in http)
changed name of Main.scala.html to MainPage.scala.html due to upper/lowercase problems with main.scala.html/Main.scala.html
Implemented registration form: visit /business_signup or go to Login > No account yet?
